# Kubernetes & OpenShift Labeling Standards

## Overview

This rule defines labeling and annotation conventions for all Kubernetes resources in this project, following:
- [Kubernetes recommended labels](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/overview/working-with-objects/common-labels/)
- [Guidelines for Labels and Annotations for OpenShift Applications](https://github.com/redhat-developer/app-labels/blob/master/labels-annotation-for-openshift.adoc)
- [OpenShift 4.20 Topology View](https://docs.redhat.com/en/documentation/openshift_container_platform/4.20/html-single/building_applications/index#odc-viewing-application-composition-using-topology-view)

## Required Kubernetes Labels

All resources MUST include these labels (REC = Recommended per Red Hat guidelines):

| Label | Status | Purpose | Example |
|-------|--------|---------|---------|
| `app.kubernetes.io/part-of` | REC | Groups resources in OpenShift Topology view | `llm-serving` |
| `app.kubernetes.io/name` | REC | Identifies the component name | `mistral-3-int4` |
| `app.kubernetes.io/component` | REC | Identifies the component role | `inference`, `database` |
| `app.kubernetes.io/instance` | REC | Unique name identifying this instance (when different from `name`) | `mistral-3-int4-private-ai` |

Label values MUST be under 63 characters and valid per [Kubernetes naming rules](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/overview/working-with-objects/labels/#syntax-and-character-set).

## Optional Kubernetes Labels

| Label | Purpose | Example |
|-------|---------|---------|
| `app.kubernetes.io/version` | Current version of the component | `"3.0"`, `"0.13.0"` |
| `app.kubernetes.io/managed-by` | Tool managing the component | `argocd`, `kserve`, `odh` |

## Naming Convention for `app.kubernetes.io/part-of`

Use **short, functional group names** (not step numbers):

| Group | Value | Resources |
|-------|-------|-----------|
| **LLM Serving** | `llm-serving` | InferenceService, ServingRuntime, vLLM pods |
| **RAG** | `rag` | LlamaStack, PostgreSQL (pgvector), Docling, chatbot, ingestion |
| **Guardrails** | `guardrails` | GuardrailsOrchestrator, HAP detector, prompt injection detector |
| **MCP Integration** | `mcp-integration` | database-mcp, openshift-mcp, slack-mcp, MCP PostgreSQL |
| **Observability** | `observability` | Grafana, ServiceMonitors, Dashboards |
| **Benchmarking** | `benchmarking` | GuideLLM CronJob, Jobs, Pipelines, Workbench |
| **Model Registry** | `model-registry` | ModelRegistry, MariaDB, seed jobs |
| **GPU Infrastructure** | `gpu-infra` | NFD, GPU Operator, MachineSets |
| **Kueue Quotas** | `kueue` | ClusterQueue, LocalQueue, ResourceFlavor |
| **Storage** | `storage` | MinIO deployment, buckets, routes |

## Values for `app.kubernetes.io/component`

Standard values from the [Red Hat app-labels guide](https://github.com/redhat-developer/app-labels/blob/master/labels-annotation-for-openshift.adoc), extended with AI-specific roles:

| Value | Description | Examples in this demo |
|-------|-------------|----------------------|
| `inference` | Model serving endpoints | InferenceService, ServingRuntime |
| `backend` | Application logic / API services | LlamaStack, chatbot, docling, MCP servers |
| `database` | Data persistence | PostgreSQL, MariaDB, MinIO |
| `frontend` | User-facing UI | Grafana dashboards, rag-chatbot |
| `monitoring` | Observability components | Grafana operator, ServiceMonitors, DCGM dashboards |
| `orchestrator` | Workflow coordination | GuardrailsOrchestrator, DSPA |
| `detector` | Safety / classification models | HAP detector, prompt injection detector |
| `integration` | API gateways, middleware | Ingestion service, MCP server proxies |
| `cache` | Caching layer | (not used in this demo) |
| `queue` | Message queuing | (not used in this demo) |

## OpenShift-Specific Labels

These labels power features in the OpenShift Console Topology view. Apply to Deployments, Services, Routes, BuildConfigs, and other visible resources.

| Label | Status | Purpose | Example |
|-------|--------|---------|---------|
| `app.openshift.io/runtime` | REC | Displays a recognizable icon in Topology (matched against a [predefined icon set](https://docs.redhat.com/en/documentation/openshift_container_platform/4.20/html-single/building_applications/index)) | `postgresql`, `python`, `grafana` |
| `app.openshift.io/runtime-version` | OPT | Runtime version display | `"16"`, `"3.12"` |

### Runtime values for this demo

| Component | `app.openshift.io/runtime` |
|-----------|---------------------------|
| PostgreSQL (steps 04, 07, 10) | `postgresql` |
| MinIO (step-03) | `golang` |
| Docling (step-07) | `python` |
| rag-chatbot (step-07) | `python` |
| ingestion-service (step-07) | `python` |
| Grafana (step-06) | `grafana` |
| vLLM InferenceServices (step-05) | `python` |
| MCP servers (step-10) | `golang` |

## OpenShift-Specific Annotations

These annotations add interactivity to the Topology view. Apply to the primary resource of each component (typically the Deployment or DeploymentConfig).

| Annotation | Status | Purpose | Example |
|------------|--------|---------|---------|
| `app.openshift.io/connects-to` | OPT | Draws dependency arrows between components in Topology | `'["postgresql","minio"]'` |
| `app.openshift.io/vcs-uri` | REC | Links component to source code from Topology view | `https://github.com/adnan-drina/rhoai3-demo.git` |
| `app.openshift.io/vcs-ref` | OPT | Branch, tag, or commit SHA for source link | `main` |

### Dependency connections for this demo

| Resource | `app.openshift.io/connects-to` |
|----------|-------------------------------|
| rag-chatbot Deployment | `'["lsd-rag"]'` |
| lsd-rag LlamaStackDistribution | `'["llamastack-postgres","granite-8b-agent"]'` |
| database-mcp Deployment | `'["mcp-postgresql"]'` |
| guardrails-orchestrator | `'["hap-detector","prompt-injection-detector","granite-8b-agent"]'` |
| model-registry | `'["model-registry-db"]'` |
| ingestion-service Job | `'["docling","llamastack-postgres"]'` |

### Source code annotation for custom-built components

Apply `vcs-uri` and `vcs-ref` to components that have BuildConfigs or source in this repo:

```yaml
metadata:
  annotations:
    app.openshift.io/vcs-uri: https://github.com/adnan-drina/rhoai3-demo.git
    app.openshift.io/vcs-ref: main
```

Applicable to: `rag-chatbot`, `ingestion-service`.

## Full Label and Annotation Example

```yaml
metadata:
  labels:
    app.kubernetes.io/name: llamastack-postgres
    app.kubernetes.io/instance: llamastack-postgres
    app.kubernetes.io/version: "16"
    app.kubernetes.io/component: database
    app.kubernetes.io/part-of: rag
    app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: argocd
    app.openshift.io/runtime: postgresql
  annotations:
    app.openshift.io/vcs-uri: https://github.com/adnan-drina/rhoai3-demo.git
```

