## Anti-Patterns (Avoid)

вқҢ **Step numbers in labels**: `app.kubernetes.io/part-of: step-07-model-performance-metrics`
вқҢ **Overly long names**: `app.kubernetes.io/part-of: guidellm-model-performance-metrics-observability`
вқҢ **Generic names**: `app.kubernetes.io/part-of: app` or `app.kubernetes.io/part-of: demo`

## ArgoCD Application Labels

ArgoCD Application objects in `gitops/argocd/app-of-apps/` use a separate label set from workload resources:

```yaml
metadata:
  labels:
    app.kubernetes.io/part-of: rhoai3-demo
    demo.rhoai.io/step: "XX"
```

These labels group all demo Applications in the ArgoCD UI. Do not use workload `part-of` values (like `llm-serving`) on Application objects.

## Migration

When updating existing resources:
1. Update the label in GitOps manifests
2. Apply via ArgoCD sync or `oc apply`
3. Verify grouping in OpenShift Console Topology view

